gomodel:SYNGO_4777  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 1,2,8: presynaptic overexpression of CACNA2D2 (α2δ-2 Calcium Channel) was enriched at synaptic puncta\n\nFigure 3,4: presynaptic overexpression of CACNA2D2 lead to increased postsynaptic GABAAR recruitment in cultured hippocampal and medium spiny neurons\n\nFigure 6: \"live-cell labeling of MSNs cotransfected with HA-tagged CACNA2D subunits and soluble\neGFP revealed that all CACNA2D isoforms are expressed on the surface of presynaptic axonal varicosities and thus can in theory contribute to synaptic functions in GABAergic neurons\"\n\nDavies A, et al. 2010 (PMID:20080692, Fig. 4G) showed CACNA2D subunits are most likely linked to the plasma membrane via GPI anchor, hence we selected \"anchored component of ... membrane\". Experimental description: M&M:\n\"Animal procedures for WT BALB/c and 2 mutant mice were performed\"\n\n\"For pβA-α2δ-2 (v1): Mouse α2δ-2 was cloned from genomic cDNA from mouse brain. Primer sequences were selected according to GenBank NM-001174049.\n...\nThis construct was then HindIII/XbaI digested and the cDNA of α2δ-2 was ligated into the pβA vector, yielding pβA-α2δ-2 (v1) (GenBank accession number MK327277)\"" , "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099029 replaced by GO:0048787" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_4777" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

